1 otherwise preempted by federal law, the expenditure of Non-
2 Locally-Sourced Funds shall be subject to appropriation by law.
3 As used in this Chapter, "Non-Locally-Sourced Funds"
4 means all funds including but not limited to pandemic relief,
5 infrastructure grants, compact impact aid, disaster recovery funds-
6 exclusive of the General Fund and other locally-sourced revenues-
7 that directly or indirectly benefit the Commonwealth of the Northern
8 Mariana Islands and originate from outside the Commonwealth,
9 including from the U.S. Federal Government or any of its agencies,
10 and are subject to expenditure by the Governor or the Office of the
11 Governor.
12 §7507. Legislative Review of Proposed Certification of Non-
13 Locally Sourced Funds. The Governor shall submit a proposed
14 certification for the expenditure or use of any Non-Locally-Sourced
15 Funds to the Legislature for review. Said certification shall be
16 submitted to the Legislature and may not be transmitted unless
17 approved by statute or joint resolution enacted into law.
18 No certification shall be considered valid or effective unless
19 it is first approved by law or joint resolution enacted by the CNMI
20 Legislature. This requirement applies to all certifications of use for
21 funds originating from federal sources, including but not limited to

HOUSE BILL 24- 21
1 Title VI of the Social Security Act (42 U.S.C. § 801 et seq.), as
2 amended.
3 §7508. Exemptions. The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply
4 to the following entities and the funds they receive or expend, except
5 where the Governor or the Office of the Governor exercises direct
6 expenditure authority:
7 1. The CNMI Public School System;
8 2. The CNMI Office of Public Auditor;
9 3. The Northern Marianas College;
10 4. All CNMI autonomous agencies and public corporations;
11 5. The Northern Marianas Housing Corporation;
12 6. Any federal funds provided directly to a specific grantee pursuant to
13 the terms of a federal grant, contract, or award, provided the grantee
14 is not the Governor or the Office of the Governor.
15 §7509. Office of Public Auditor Oversight and Audit. The Office
16 of Public Auditor shall establish a taskforce to monitor expenditure
17 of all Non-Locally-Sourced Funds for compliance with the terms of
18 the certification mandated by this Act and shall issue quarterly
19 reports on the taskforce's findings to the Legislature.
20 §7510. Unauthorized Expenditure. In addition to any other civil
21 or criminal penalties, any person who violates this Act by causing

HOUSE BILL 24- 21
1 the unauthorized expenditure of Non-Locally-Sourced Funds shall
2 be deemed to have committed a felony punishable by not less than
3 5 years and not more than 20 years imprisonment and/or a fine of
4 not less than $10,000, or both in addition to being jointly or severally
5 liable for the amounts that were expended in violation of this Act.
6 §7511. Failure to Obtain Legislative Certification. In addition to
7 any other civil or criminal penalties, any person who violates this
8 Act by failing to obtain legislative certification of Non-Locally-
9 Sourced Funds as provided by the Act, shall be deemed to have
10 committed a misdemeanor punishable by not less than 1 year and
11 not more than 5 years imprisonment and/or a fine of not less than
12 $1,000, or both in addition to being jointly or severally liable for the
13 amounts that were expended in violation of this Act."
